-President of IDU\r\nEvgenij Vajman (Israel) – The Vice-President\r\nLev Piankov (Russia) – The executive director of IDU\r\nNadejda Bantiuc (Moldova) – IDU Presidium Member\r\nOleg Kudinow (Russia) - IDU Presidium Member\r\nVladimir Karachentsev (Ukraine) - IDU Presidium Member\r\n\r\nIt was decided at the Conference to conduct the extraordinary supplementary election Conference in 2013 with the aim of including in the governing bodies representatives of new member countries.\r\n\r\nThe general directions of IDU activity in the nearest future are as follows:\r\n\r\n1. Development of the system of stimulation for dancers of all levels. Introduction of a unified database of clubs, dancers, adjudicators.\r\n2. Further development of the system of conducting of competitions: computerization of applications, analysis of judging, improvement of judging system, rotation of adjudicators at the titular events.\r\n3. Enhanced demands for granting of IDU adjudicator''s categories.\r\n4. Clear classification of IDU events.\r\n5. Approval of unified IDU rules on figures and dresses.\r\n6. Strengthening of the role and authority of IDU member organizations.\r\nThe basic principles of IDU remain the following: openness of IDU events for participation of all dancing couples, maximum objectivity for judging, supremacy for professional approach.\r\nThe IDU leadership is available for communication and invites you to become an active participant of our movement.\r\n\r\nBest regards\r\nIgor Mashyn\r\nIDU President<!--:-->', '<!--:ru-->Отчетно-выборная Конференция IDU<!--:--><!--:en-->Report-and-election Conference of IDU <!--:-->', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '158-revision-2', '', '', '2012-10-04 03:33:04', '2012-10-04 00:33:04', '', 158, 'http://idudance.com/158-revision-2/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
